4.35 pm: Twenty two wickets have fallen today, 27 is the all-time record. South Africa need 236 to win this Test. Given what has happened, it seems an improbable task. But how they have roared back into the game. They will take it. They were finished after Australia had taken a first-innings lead of 188. A chase of 400 seemed likely. Not they have to chase only 236. They will take it.

Prakash: "What amazes me most that how come Clarke managed to score 151 on this pitch where the two innings today yielded less than that,to be precise 143 runs"

Michael: "Can someone just tell me if it's the pitch that is playing bad or is it just great bowling?" This pitch is not easy to bat on. There is swing, there is seam and there is bounce. It isn't outrageous though. The bounce isn't uneven and it isn't two-paced. The bowling has been terrific, but some of the shots have been poor. Hussey's and Haddin's in particular.

Paul: "Interesting to note that this'll be the 8th instance in test history of no. 11 top scoring."

Sajan: "Opening batsman picks up most wickets. Bowler #11 top scores. bizarre"

The lowest total for a team winning a Test is 45.

Brendan: "What the hell just happened? Last time I checked it was one fer at lunch and suddenly we've castled them? What were they bowling? Hand Grenades?" Nothing explosive, just healthy wicket-to-wicket lines with a bit of movement.

This is brilliant from Steve, "I just rang tha SA scorecard - and i didn't get Adrian...."

Watson and Hughes are out there. Can Watson do it with the bat, too? Steyn's bowling from over the wicket. Three slips and a gully.
